# L2-1698: UNPACK of a Micheline tree whose primitive id is 163
# (`Create_contract`). Bytes: 0x05 PACK tag, 0x03 (prim, 0 args, no
# annots), 0xa3 (prim id 163). This is an internal-only prim MIR uses to
# unparse `operation` values; it has no on-chain binary encoding and L1's
# `prim_encoding` assigns no tag to it, so L1's decoder rejects it. MIR's
# binary decoder rejects it too (and, were it accepted, the decoded `App`
# is not a valid `int` and fails typechecking). Both implementations push
# None: this pins L1/MIR agreement at the UNPACK boundary.
code { UNPACK int } ;
input { Stack_elt bytes 0x0503a3 } ;
output { Stack_elt (option int) None }
